steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"48l89","text":"Place specimen inside the hood over dissection table and photograph prior to sampling.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7cphc","text":"Select the sites from which samples will be collected, annotate and mark (if serial sampling is done)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6g1gs","text":"Cut each of the selected regions from the previous step into 9 small chunks. Chunks should be small enough to just cover the bottom of a microfuge tube (~5mm x 5mm x 5mm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bdtnm","text":"Dab the small chunks on a sterile gauze pad and place each one into a labeled microfuge tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"al9td","text":"Place 9 small chunks into the empty tubes to be snap frozen. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7sl5l","text":"Drop tubes into liquid Nitrogen. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2slc8","text":"Leave for ~2-10 minutes. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1k8gd","text":"Remove and store in -80C freezer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e0ei0","text":"Place one piece of the selected regions into a tubes containing 20x volume of 10% formalin (to be processed into FFPE blocks). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aaoor","text":"Store in 4C fridge.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9rlu7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fbcc2","text":"Note: Fixation occurs at a rate of 1 mm per hour. Over-fixation causes tight cross-linking and under-fixation can compromise the tissue.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":136}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c7uu6","text":"Place one piece of the selected regions into a tube with cold DMEM with anti/anti.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"mnug","text":"Store in 4C fridge. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"808bs","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"afibj","text":"Process as soon as possible.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":28}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d2ecl","text":"(OPTIONAL - If needed) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3p4re","text":"Wash the full-thickness core in cold PBS in a petri dish.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ane2k","text":"Make a notation of the time the sample went into formalin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bbb4l","text":"Based on the size of the tissue, fix the required length of time (4 to 24 hours).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4rqgj","text":"After the fixation period, remove the cassette and place in 70% ETOH until scheduled processing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
